{
  "texts": [
    "The Z ′ mass is set to M Z ′ = 1 TeV. 4.",
    "111Exclusive lepton flavour conserving b → sℓ + ℓ -modes The simplest process induced by b → sℓ + ℓ -is the purely leptonic B s decay, that we analyse using f Bs = 230.3 ± 1.3 MeV[5].",
    "Fig. 7 shows the branching fractions B(B s → µ + µ -) and B(B s → τ + τ -) for M Z ′ = 1 TeV and 3 TeV.",
    "In SM we find B(B s → µ + µ -) = (3.65 ± 0.10) × 10 -9 (|λ * ts |/0.04) 2 and B(B s → τ + τ -) = (7.70 ± 0.10) × 10 -7 (|λ * ts |/0.04) 2.",
    "The experimental world average B(B s → µ + µ -) exp = (3.34±0.27)×10 -9 [30] is indicated in Fig. 7."
  ]
}